From 340eb285b6d986e91969a1170d7fe9b0face405e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Date: Mon, 19 Jan 2026 15:10:32 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Security fix for CVE-2026-23745

Fix: Properly sanitize absolute paths in both 'path' and 'linkpath' fields
to prevent path traversal vulnerabilities

This patch addresses a security vulnerability by ensuring that symbolic
link targets are validated with the same rigor as regular file paths.
The fix extracts path validation logic into a reusable method that strips
absolute path prefixes and checks for directory traversal attempts.

Reference: https://github.com/isaacs/node-tar/security/advisories/GHSA-8qq5-rm4j-mr97
